  "name": "cache_lru_eviction_arbos60",
  "description": "Mirrors program_test.go::TestWasmLruCache. Capacity is shrunk via ArbOwner.setWasmMaxStylusFragments to a low value, then three programs A/B/C are activated and invoked in sequence. Reinvoking A should miss the LRU cache (B/C displaced it), forcing a recompile from the long-term cache and asserted via gas delta vs. warm reinvoke. Runs at ArbOS v60 so the v60-only RecentWASMs block-local cache also becomes observable. Placeholder l2Msg strings need 3x WASM bytes + ArbOwner setter calldata + signed deploys + signed invokes.",
